# Documentation Style - SpaceBooker

> **Example**: This is a filled-in doc style rule for a project.

## Principles

1. **Minimal**: Don't document obvious things
2. **Current**: Stale docs are worse than no docs
3. **Scannable**: Headers, bullets, tables - no walls of text
4. **For AI**: AGENTS.md is primary context for AI agents

## File Types

| File | Purpose | Location | Update When |
|------|---------|----------|-------------|
| AGENTS.md | AI context | Root | Patterns/stack change |
| Feature README | How feature works | docs/features/ | Feature changes |
| ADR | Why we decided | docs/decisions/ | Never (immutable) |
| INDEX.md | Navigation | docs/ | New docs added |

## AGENTS.md Structure

Core sections (50-80 lines, 150 max):

1. **Overview** - What project does (1-2 sentences)
2. **Stack** - Technologies and versions (table)
3. **Commands** - Install, dev, test, build
4. **Structure** - File organization (tree)
5. **Context Loading** - References to detailed docs
6. **Boundaries** - Always / Ask First / Never rules

