## Formatting Rules

### Code Blocks

Always specify language:

```typescript
const user = await getUser(id);
```

Not:

```
const user = await getUser(id);
```

### Tables

Keep to 3-4 columns max:

| Good | Better | Best |
|------|--------|------|
| x | y | z |

### Diagrams vs Tables

| Context | Use |
|---------|-----|
| AI-read (AGENTS.md) | Tables |
| Human-read (READMEs) | Mermaid |

Mermaid for complex flows:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    User --> API --> DB
```

### Links

Use relative paths:

```markdown
See [auth docs](../features/auth/README.md)
```

## Don't Document

- Obvious code behavior
- Things that change frequently
- Implementation details
- Duplicates of existing docs

## When to Update

| Event | Update |
|-------|--------|
| Tech stack change | AGENTS.md → Stack |
| File structure change | AGENTS.md → Structure |
| New context sources | AGENTS.md → Context Loading |
| New boundary rules | AGENTS.md → Boundaries |
| Feature complete | Feature README |
| Architecture decision | ADR |
